        "answer_count": 2,
        "title": "Java regex - split string with leading special characters",
        "body": "<p>I am trying to split a string that contains whitespaces and special characters. The string starts with special characters.\nWhen I run the code, the first array element is an empty string.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>String s = \",hm  ..To?day,.. is not T,uesday.\";\nString[] sArr = s.split(\"[^a-zA-Z]+\\\\s*\");\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Expected result is <code>[\"hm\", \"To\", \"day\", \"is\", \"not\", \"T\", \"uesday\"]<\/code><\/p>\n\n<p>Can someone explain how this is happening?<\/p>\n\n<p>Actual result is <code>[\"\", \"hm\", \"To\", \"day\", \"is\", \"not\", \"T\", \"uesday\"]<\/code><\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 56959653,
        "tags": [
            "java",
            "regex",
            "split"
        ],
