        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/d84b558fd67be10d5a718fb94231909d?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 93689,
                "user_type": "moderator",
                "user_id": 256196,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/256196/bohemian",
                "reputation": 427464,
                "display_name": "Bohemian",
                "accept_rate": 77
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 2,
            "is_accepted": true,
            "last_activity_date": 1562703437,
            "creation_date": 1562703108,
            "body": "<p>Split is behaving as expected by splitting off a zero-length string at the start before the first comma.<\/p>\n\n<p>To fix, first remove all splitting chars from the start:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>String[] sArr = s.replaceAll(\"^([^a-zA-Z]*\\\\s*)*\", \"\").split(\"[^a-zA-Z]+\\\\s*\");\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Note that I\u2019ve altered the removal regex to trim any sequence of spaces and non-letters from the front.<\/p>\n\n<p>You don\u2019t need to remove from the tail because split discards empty trailing elements from the result.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 56959902,
            "question_id": 56959653,
            "last_edit_date": 1562703437
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/2Zxuq.png?s=256",
                "account_id": 2521234,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 2191572,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2191572/monkeyzeus",
                "reputation": 20801,
                "display_name": "MonkeyZeus",
                "accept_rate": 69
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 1,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1562702778,
            "creation_date": 1562702778,
            "body": "<p>I would simplify it by making it a two-step process rather than trying to achieve a pure regex <code>split()<\/code> operation:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>s.replaceAll( '[^a-zA-Z]+', ' ' ).trim().split( ' ' )\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 56959846,
            "question_id": 56959653
        }
